        <abstract> 
<p>AG’s review of Alphonse de Candolle’s paper [<hi rend="italic">Am. J. Sci.</hi> 2d ser. 35 (1863): 430–44] is excellent.</p> 
            <p>Does not AG consider that orchids oppose Oswald Heer’s view that species arise suddenly by monstrosities?</p>
            <p>Infers that AG cannot explain the angles of phyllotaxy; has been looking at Carl Nägeli on the subject.</p>
            <p>Reports Gaston de Saporta’s belief that natural selection will ultimately triumph in France.</p> 
<p>Is working slowly at <hi rend="italic">Variation</hi>.</p>  
<p>Reports his observations on the imperfect flowers of <hi rend="italic">Viola</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Oxalis</hi>.</p> 
        </abstract>
